value.value: Pezones implantandos altos

definition.value: Placement of the nipples at a higher than normal location.

value.value: Disminución del nivel de caveolina-3 muscular
The amount of calveolin-3 in muscle tissue is below the lower limit of normal.

label.value: Abnormal tissue enzyme concentration or activity

value.value: Concentración o actividad anormal de enzimas tisulares.

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: Abnormal tissue enzyme concentration or activity

definition.value: Concentration of an enyzme in a tissue is above or between the limit of normal. This term is intended to be used for enzymes that can be measured in multiple tissues other than blood.
For enzymes measured in the blood circulation, the term Abnormal circulating enzyme concentration or activity should be used.

value.value: Necrosis esplénica
Cell dealth (necrosis) located in the spleen.

definition.value: CT of the abdomen can be used to investigate splenic necrosis.

value.value: Tumor carcinoide del páncreas
A carcinoid tumor of the pancreas (CTP) is a rare neuroendocrine tumor arising from the serotonin-secreting cells (enterochromaffin or Kultscitsky's cells).
de ácido dihidroxifenilacético en sangre
The concentration of dihydroxyphenylacetic acid in the blood circulation is above the upper limit of normal.
Concentración inapropiadamente baja de acetoacetato.

definition.value: Lower than appropriate concentration of acetoacetate in states such as hypoglycemia in which the normal response would be to elevate acetoacetate.

Ketone synthesis in the liver produces acetoacetate and beta-hydroxybutyrate from two acetyl CoA molecules. This occurs during ketoacidosis in physiological (starvation) and disease-associated (diabetic ketoacidosis) states.

value.value: Concentración apropiadamente baja de beta-hidroxibutirato

definition.value: Lower than appropriate concentration of beta-hydroxybutyrate in states such as hypoglycemia in which the normal response would be to elevate acetoacetate.

Ketone synthesis in the liver produces acetoacetate and beta-hydroxybutyrate from two acetyl CoA molecules. This occurs during ketoacidosis in physiological (starvation) and disease-associated (diabetic ketoacidosis) states.

value.value: Aumento de la concentración de 3-hidroxibutiril-carnitina en sangre
Concentration of 3-hydroxybutyryl-carnitine in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal.
Aumento de la concentración de 5-amino-4-imidazolcarboxiamida en el líquido cefalorraquídeo

definition.value: The concentration of 5-amino-4-imidazolecarboxyamide in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) is above the upper limit of normal.

value.value: Aumento de la concentración del factor de necrosis tumoral alfa en sangre

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: Elevated circulating tumor necrosis factor alpha concentration

label.value: Elevated circulating tumor necrosis factor alpha concentration

value.value: The concentration of tumor necrosis factor alpha in the blood circulation is above the upper limit of normal.
Reducción de la actividad circulante de la pirimidina 5-prime-nucleotidasa
The activity of concentration of pyrimidine 5-prime-nucleotidase (EC 3.1.3.5) in the blood circulation is below the lower limit of normal.

label.value: Diminished prolactin response to thyrotrophin-releasing hormone stimulation

value.value: Disminución de la respuesta de la prolactina a la estimulación de la hormona liberadora de tirotrofina

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: Diminished prolactin response to thyrotrophin-releasing hormone stimulation

value.value: The increase in prolactin concentration (PRL) following stimulation with thyrotropin (thyrdoid releasing hormone) as compared to baseline PRL concentration is below the lower limit of normal.
Disminución de la concentración del componente 1 del complemento en sangre

definition.value: The concentration of complement component 1s (C1s) in the blood circulation is below the lower limit of normal.

value.value: Reducción de la concentración de globulina fijadora de cortisol en sangre
The concentration of cortisol-binding globulin in the blood circulation is below the lower limit of normal.
Disminución de la concentración de tiroglobulina en sangre

definition.value: The concentration of thyroglobulin in the blood circulation is below the lower limit of normal.

value.value: Aumento de la concentración del factor estimulante de colonias de granulocitos y macrófagos en sangre

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: Elevated circulating granulocyte-macrophage colony-stimulating factor concentration

label.value: Elevated circulating granulocyte-macrophage colony-stimulating factor concentration

value.value: The concentration of granulocyte-macrophage colony-stimulating factor (GM-CSF) in the blood circulation is above the upper limit of normal.
Aumento de la concentración de ácido D-2-hidroxiglutárico en líquido cefalorraquídeo
The concentration of D-2-hydroxyglutaric acid in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) is above the upper limit of normal.
Masa esofágica

definition.value: A swelling or enlargement localized to the esophagus. The word mass is usually used at an early stage of the diagnostic workup before the precise nature of the swelling has been determined.

value.value: Cristales en líquido sinovial
The presence of crystals (microscopic solids that form distinct lattices, with definable fixed angles, faces, walls) in the joint (synovial) fluid.

definition.value: Polarized light microscope is the standard method for synovial fluid analysis in the search for crystals. Identification of monosodium urate and calcium pyrophosphate crystals in synovial fluid samples obtained from inflamed joints allows the precise diagnosis of gout and calcium pyrophosphate dehydrate crystal related arthropathy

value.value: Pliegues gástricos agrandados
Giant gastric folds are recognized at endoscopy as an increase in the size of the gastric rugae and a lack of flattening.

definition.value: The most common causes of giant gastric folds are Menetrier disease, acute gastric mucosal lesions, gastric lymphoma, and scirrhous carcinoma.

value.value: Linfocitosis intraepitelial gástrica
The count of lymphocytes located in the epithelial layer of the gastric mucosa is above the upper limit of normal.
Linfocitosis intraepitelial del intestino delgado
The count of lymphocytes located in the epithelial layer of the mucosa of the small intestine is above the upper limit of normal.
Hiperecogenicidad pulmonar fetal
Increased response (echo) of lung tissue of a fetus observed on prenatal sonography. Increased echo response is conventially displayed as a higher degree of brightness.

definition.value: The ultrasonographic appearance of fetal lung hyperechogenicity is most commonly associated with congenital bronchopulmonary abnormalities, such as cystic adenomatoid malformation or pulmonary lobar sequestration.

value.value: Vasculitis necrotizante
A histopathological finding characterized by inflammation of the arterial and/or capillary and/or venous blood vessels, leading to a change in the vascular wall as a whole.

definition.value: Stenosis or occlusion of the vascular lumen by thrombosis or intimal proliferation is the result of endothelial damage, which is the cause of clinical manifestations. This finding may be observed with a group of diseases including polyarteritis nodosa and anti-neutrophil cytoplasmic antibody-associated vasculitis (ANCA): granulomatosis with polyangiitis, eosinophilic granulomatosis with polyangiitis, and microscopic polyangiitis.

value.value: Morfología anormal del túbulo contorneado proximal

definition.value: Any structural anomaly of the proximal convoluted tubule, which is the first tubular component of the nephron and arises as a continuation of the Bowman space from the tubular pole of the renal corpuscle. The proximal convoluted tubule is located within the renal cortex.

value.value: Presencia de Leishmania en tejido

definition.value: Presence of Leishmania, a parasitic protozoan, in a tissue specimen. Leishmania is responsible for leishmaniasis.
Leishmania may be detected in tissues such as bone marrow, spleen, liver, or skin by methods including Wright or Giemsa stain.

value.value: Quistes de Pneumocystis en secreciones respiratorias.
Demonstration of cysts of Pneumocystis (a genus of related fungal species) in respiratory secretions such as nasopharyngeal secretions or pleural fluid.
Granuloma de médula espinal
An aggregation of macrophages (forming in response to chronic inflammation) localized in or on the spinal cord.
Absorción alterada de folato
Reduced ability to absorb folate in the diet. This finding can be measured by a folic acid loading test in which blood concentration of folate is measured after oral administration of folic acid.
Prueba de aliento de hidrógeno positiva

Abnormally elevated quantiy of hydrogen measured by a hydrogen breath test (HBT). HBTs administer substrates such as glucose, lactulose, lactose and fructose and subsequently measure hydrogen exhaled in the breath using a gas chromatograph.

definition.value: Bacteria, especially anaerobic, colonizing the large bowel in health and small bowel in diseased conditions produce hydrogen by fermentation of unabsorbed carbohydrates. Though small amount of hydrogen is produced from limited amounts of unabsorbed carbohydrate reaching the colon, large amounts of hydrogen may be produced if there is malaborption of carbohydrate in the small intestine allowing larger amount to reach the colon or if there is excess of bacteria in the small bowel. The hydrogen produced by the bacteria is absorbed through the wall of the small or large intestine or both. The hydrogen-containing blood travels to the lungs where the hydrogen is released and exhaled in the breath where it can be measured.

value.value: Antecedente reciente de pinchazo en la piel con espinas de plantas.

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: History of recent plant thorn skin puncture

label.value: History of recent plant thorn skin puncture

definition.value: A history of a plant skin puncture preceding the current presenting condition by hours, days, or weeks.

value.value: Ausencia de cadena kappa de inmunoglobulina en sangre
Nondetectable kappa chain in the blood circulation.

definition.value: Human immunoglobulin molecules are built up by a pair of identical heavy chains, identifying the immunoglobulin class (namely Gamma, Alpha, Mu, Delta and Epsilon), and by a pair of identical light chains, Kappa or Lambda alternatively, character- izing the immunoglobulin type. In humans, under normal condi- tions, Kappa light chains represent approximately 2/3 of the light chains of total immunoglobulins, both circulating and lymphocyte surface bound.

value.value: Pseudoglioma
A circumscribed whitish-yellow mass in the posterior chamber associated with retinal folds and sometimes retinal detachment and is said to resemble a retinal glioma.
Edema dérmico papilar
Swelling due to fluid acculuation of the papillary dermis.

definition.value: The dermis has two major layers: the upper papillary dermis and the lower reticular dermis. The papillary dermis: The papillary dermis consists of bundles of collagen fibrils and oxytalan elastic fibers, ans is separated from the lower reticular dermis by a subpapillary plexus.

value.value: Taquicardia fetal
The number of beats per minute (bpm) of the fetal heart is above the upper limit of the normal for the gestational age. Fetal tachycardia is thus defined as a heart rate greater than 160-180 bpm.

definition.value: In the first trimester of pregnancy, the fetal heart rate (FHR)increases from 125 beats per minute (bpm) at 6 weeks to about175 bpm at 9 weeks, followed by a gradual decrease to about160 bpm at 14 weeks, noted in fetuses conceived by assisted reproductive procedures.

value.value: Aumento del nivel de 3-hidroxiquinurenina en orina
The amount of 3-hydroxykynurenine in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.
Aciduria 2-oxoadípica
The amount of 2-oxoadipic acid in the urine, normaliyed for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.
Aumento de la concentración de sulfóxido de metionina en sangre

definition.value: The concentration of methionine sulfoxide in the blood circulation is above the upper limit of normal.
Methionine S-oxide is a derivative of methionine and is a biomarker of oxidative stress.

value.value: Aumento de la concentración de ácido pipecólico en sangre

definition.value: The concentration of pipecolic acid in the blood circulation is above the upper limit of normal.

value.value: Aumento del nivel de ácido pipecólico en orina

definition.value: The amount of pipecolic acid in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

value.value: Aumento de la concentración de sacaropina en el líquido cefalorraquídeo

definition.value: Concentration of saccharopine in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) above the upper limit of normal.

value.value: Aumento de la concentración de glicilprolina en sangre

definition.value: Concentration in the bloodstream of glycylproline above the upper limit of normal. Glycylproline is a dipeptide composed of glycine and proline, and is an end product of collagen metabolism that is further cleaved by prolidase (EC 3.4.13.9).

value.value: Aumento de la concentración de octanoilcarnitina en sangre

definition.value: Concentration of octanoylcarnitine (C8:0) in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal.
C8: octanoylcarnitine high in blood

value.value: Aumento de la concentración de decanoilcarnitina en sangre

definition.value: Concentration of decanoylcarnitine (C10:0) in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal.

value.value: Aciduria 2-hidroxifenilacética

definition.value: Increased concentration of 2-hydroxyphenylacetic acid in the urine.

value.value: Aciduria 4-hidroxifenilláctica

definition.value: Amount of 4-hydroxyphenyllactic acid in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

value.value: Aumento de la concentración de beta-alanina en el líquido cefalorraquídeo

definition.value: The concentration of beta-alanine present in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) is above the upper limit of normal.

value.value: Aumento de la concentración de ácido 2-aminoadípico en sangre
The concentration of 2-aminoadipic acid in the blood circulation is above the upper limit of normal.
Aumento del nivel de N-carbamoil-beta-alanina en orina

definition.value: The amount of N-carbamoyl-beta-alanine present in urine, when adjusted for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.
